utton\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ldo1665702725085.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ldo1665702725085.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ldo1665702725085.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ldo1665702725085\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      tls server validation\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Instruct the LDAP connector to connect to the LDAP server using TLS.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__topic_d51299e1_d51300e1_d51301e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__p_d51302e1_d51303e1_d51304e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$LDP_PARAMS</code> { <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code> } <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tls server validation</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">validate</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">v</code>} | {<code class=\"ph codeph\">ignore_name</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">in</code>}</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__p_d51305e1_d51306e1_d51307e1\">Values can be combined using <code class=\"ph codeph\">+</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">&amp;</code>. For example:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__li_d24431e1_d24432e1_d24433e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$LDP_PARAMS = tls server validation=valid+ignore_name</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__li_d24434e1_d24435e1_d24436e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$LDP_PARAMS tlssv=v&amp;in</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__li_d24437e1_d24438e1_d24439e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$LDP_PARAMS tlssv=ignore_name</code>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__section_em4_cgg_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d987265e112\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__ul_s4r_dgg_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__li_d24440e1_d24441e1_d24442e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">validate</code> or\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">v</code>—use TLS and validate the server by checking its certificate and\n               validating the server name. (Default) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__li_d24443e1_d24444e1_d24445e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ignore_name</code> or\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">in</code>—check the certificate but do not validate the server name.\n            </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__section_wrf_2gg_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d987265e137\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__p_d51314e1_d51315e1_d51316e1\">For Windows,\n            the CA certificate must be placed in the Windows Certificate Trust Store in the client,\n            so that the server's certificate can be validated.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ldo1665702725085__p_d51317e1_d51318e1_d51319e1\">For Unix, the location is\n            specified by either the option <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tls_ca_file</span> or the option <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tls\n               ca directory</span>. Either of these settings will implicitly set <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tls\n               server validation</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=validate</code>, if the option is not specified. For more information, see\n               <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tya1665702725016.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tya1665702725016.html\" title=\"On Unix, specify the location of the CA certificate used to validate the LDAP server.\">tls ca file | directory</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pqn1665702774521.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>LDAP over TLS</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529516\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529516\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "tls server validation Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 tls server validation Instruct the LDAP connector to connect to the LDAP server using TLS. USYS$LDP_PARAMS { = } tls server validation = { validate | v } | { ignore_name | in } Values can be combined using + or & . For example: USYS$LDP_PARAMS = tls server validation=valid+ignore_name USYS$LDP_PARAMS tlssv=v&in USYS$LDP_PARAMS tlssv=ignore_name Arguments validate or v —use TLS and validate the server by checking its certificate and validating the server name. (Default) ignore_name or in —check the certificate but do not validate the server name. Description For Windows, the CA certificate must be placed in the Windows Certificate Trust Store in the client, so that the server's certificate can be validated. For Unix, the location is specified by either the option tls_ca_file or the option tls ca directory . Either of these settings will implicitly set tls server validation =validate , if the option is not specified. For more information, see tls ca file | directory . Related Links LDAP over TLS Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}